'''''Battleship Bismarck: Operation Rhine - May 1941''''' is a 1987 video game published by [[General Quarters Software]].

==Gameplay==
''Battleship Bismarck'' is a game in which one player is German Admiral [[Günther Lütjens|Lutjens]] commanding the ''[[German battleship Bismarck|Bismarck]]'' to raid Atlantic commercial ships while the other player is British Admiral [[John Tovey, 1st Baron Tovey|Tovey]] trying to sink the Bismarck.<ref name="CGW74"/>

==Reception==
Wyatt Lee reviewed the game for ''[[Computer Gaming World]]'', and compared it to ''Action in the North Atlantic'' and stated that "players who like one of these games will definitely like the other."<ref name="CGW74">{{cite magazine |last=Lee |first=Wyatt |title=Cruisers, Convoys and the Cost of Command: Two World War II Naval Games |magazine=Computer Gaming World |date=September 1990 |volume=1 |issue=74 |pages=38, 46, 62}}</ref>

The book ''The PC Games Bible'' said that "The centre point is the recreation of the gunnery battle between the Bismarck and the HMS Hood and Prince of Wales, but unlimited 'what-if' scenarios can be created."<ref>{{cite book |last1=Matthews |first1=Robin |last2=Rigby |first2=Paul |date=1992 |title=The PC Games Bible |url=https://archive.org/details/pcgamesbible0000matt/page/244/mode/2up |location=Wilmslow, Cheshire |publisher=Sigma Press |via=[[Internet Archive]] |page=244 |isbn=1-85058-332-3 |accessdate=2024-03-05 }}</ref>

